metadata.name: Bistable Perception #230
metadata.description:
Visually ambiguous patterns are the primary texture that pervade each iteration. Subtle gradients imbued with grainy noise color each fracture. A deliberate balance is struck between negative space and dense pockets of visual chaos. A gradual process of refinement that almost masks an oscillation between two modes of being.

--------

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

Warning: This piece is CPU intensive, it may not render on lower end devices.

metadata.name: Wobble Telescope #32
metadata.description:
Since the last results, we have been able to raise some funds to acquire better equipment 
for space observation and mapping.

This new telescope technology allows us to go further into our research.
We are able to observe gravitational warping and bendings.
Each researcher will be assigned to a random sector scope.


We noticed that some kind of interferences may show up on the scope:

-invisible matter vortex that twirls around, bending the surrounding gravity
-recursive vertical signal distorsion
-recursive horizontal signal distorsion
-recursive white rescan 
-central distorsion
-wormholes may spawn in some sectors, they take a long time to fully form.

It is advised to conduct the research in fullscreen mode as the images will be clearer.

To download high resolution pngs:

-click "open" under the image preview
-click on the image
-press either E for 2k resolution or R for 4k resolution
-wait for the download window (it could take a while)
-accept and save the png file

To download .txt with details and lore:

-click "open" under the image preview
-click on the image
-press T
-wait for the download window 
-accept and save the .txt file

metadata.name: Gliese 667 CC. A space atlas #25
metadata.description:
Gliese 667 CC. A space atlas
2048x2048 Generative maps.

Instructions:

Once the iteration is minted/generated, the scanning process starts, generating one layer at the time.
Wait for the scan to finish by checking the status on the bottom border of the iteration, it could take a while.
Once the scan is done, the unique name of the map will show up and this indicates the completion of the generation.
Click open under the iteration preview for full resolution view/better details.

Interactivity and Lore:

Click open under the iteration preview to go fullscreen.
Click on the image to make sure the canvas is in focus.
Press S to save a low-res png, accept download.
Press E to save a high-res png, wait for the rendering to finish, accept download. {PRINTABLE}
Press T to download the Reference.txt text with the full lore, accept download.

metadata.name: Cube on Cube #72
metadata.description:
This token generates a plottable SVG file, a different arrangement of cubes.
The cubes are designed in 2D view, then placed next to each other or on top of each other in eight different directions. The goal is to challenge the audience's mind to discover the holes or protrusions produced by placing the cubes together.
To produce random parts made of cubes, those in the same direction are merged together, which is a turning point in this project.
Do you need a different output from your piece?  Then use controllers!

Controllers 
G - Change light direction
F - Add/remove frame
L - Add/remove base lines
D - Change base lines direction
R - Reset to default settings
P - Save as PNG
S - Export high resolution SVG

Note : When you have a piece with many shapes, controllers may run delayed. (Depending on your device).

Made by p5.js

metadata.name: The City #250
metadata.description:
// The City //

Cities are the most complex human-made interventions on Earth. The human settlements are growing like huge organisms – and the growth is often impossible to plan, control or limit.
Cities as a phenomenon are with their incredible complexity highly enigmatic structures, that are as fascinating as they are terrifying.

This project is a study of the beauty of complexity.

Each city iteration is an entirely unique structure with unique hatching, arrangement of buildings, heights, sizes, additions and rare items.
The cities are made even more organic by the meticulous modelling of analog ink drawing.

The project is 100% generative. All lines, hatching and dots are generated for each iteration.

As a gesture of appreciation towards our supporters, 20% of royalties will go to the original minter.

Key commands:
Press 's' to save a png version
Press '2' to render at twice the resolution
Press 'b' to remove the colored background before saving

The loading progress is animated, hence the epileptic trigger warning.
Due to memory constraints on mobile devices, rendering uses a lower resolution on these.
-----------

Original concept by @Lax_raven
All code by @r1b2art

metadata.name: golf #41
metadata.description:
This artwork is named 'golf' due to its structure and colors. The generated abstract and random pattern may evoke a golf course - the points symbolize the golf balls and the triangular shapes, the flag of each hole. The colors used, both calming and vibrant, recall the green grass of golf courses and the surrounding natural elements.

Press "s" to save a png

metadata.name: Chroma-Ville #31
metadata.description:
Each output is generated by layering Blender renders.

The prefix 'Chroma' refers to the large color palette used in the Chroma series.

'Chroma-Ville' is the final creation in the 'Chroma' series. The arrangement of cubes creates an image reminiscent of a city-scape. Coupled with the carefully balanced colors, each output forms a bold, striking design.

In live mode:
Click/tap the image to make a "Download image" button appear. Click this button to download a 1500x2000px PNG.
